{"SHOULD":[{"def":"Used as an auxiliary verb, to express a conditional or contingent act or state, or as a supposition of an actual fact; also, to express moral obligation (see Shall); e.","pos":""}],"SHOULDER":[{"def":"The joint, or the region of the joint, by which the fore limb is connected with the body or with the shoulder girdle; the projection formed by the bones and muscles about that joint.","pos":""},{"def":"The angle of a bastion included between the face and flank.","pos":""}],"SHOULDER-SHOTTEN":[{"def":"Sprained in the shoulder, as a horse.","pos":""}],"SHOULDERED":[{"def":"Having shoulders; -- used in composition; as, a broad- shouldered man.","pos":""}],"SHOUT":[{"def":"To utter a sudden and loud outcry, as in joy, triumph, or exultation, or to attract attention, to animate soldiers, etc.","pos":""}]}